g.text: Slow Pointer is moving with one step at a time.
Fast Pointer is moving with two step at a time.
If Fast Pointer becomes NULL That means there is no loop.
But if there is a loop then there will be a point where slow pointer will be equal to fast pointer.
Then Take two pointers one to head and one at the same meeting position and move with one step at a time.
Where they meet is the starting of loop. (proof is very IMPORTANT)
Where n is the size of loop and D is the distance covered by respective Pointers.
As We Know Fast Pointer is Running at twice the speed of Slow Pointer So it will cover twice Distance.So,
and p2 will cover K*n + z
